<body>
    <h1>Versioning and Backwards Compatability</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h3 id=3D"VersioningandBackwardsCompatability-Versioning">Versionin=
g</h3>
<p>Semantic version should be honoured, and backwards compatibility should =
be ensured where possible.</p>
<ul>
<li>Patch version: Minor changes such as descriptions, formatting, addition=
al enums, addition of new fields</li>
<li>Minor version: Addition of new resources or operations</li>
<li>Major version: A breaking change that typically requires a new API</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p>Westpac Mesh APIs honour <a href=3D"https://semver.org/" class=3D"extern=
al-link" rel=3D"nofollow">semantic versioning</a> principles in that a new =
major version is not guaranteed to be backwardly compatible with a prior ma=
jor version, a new minor version is backwardly compatible with a prior mino=
r version, a new patch version is backwardly compatible with a prior patch =
version.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Westpac Mesh APIs supports both <strong>URL versioning</strong> and <str=
ong>Media type versioning.&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(1,55,85);"><strong>URL versioning</strong> is =
on by default </span>in which include the major version number in the URI w=
hich allows side by side deployment of different major versions of an API&n=
bsp;</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/MESH/Solution+O=
ptions+-+API+Versioning" rel=3D"nofollow">Media type versioning</a> is avai=
lable for Open API 3.0 and&nbsp; is a flexible solution for versioning endp=
oints without creating a new major version of an API.</p>
<ul>
<li>It allows versioning individual API endpoints when you need it.</li>
<li>You can version input and output schemas independently.</li>
</ul>
<p>Media type versioning allows the old endpoint to be marked as deprecated=
 and a new endpoint to be created in the same version of the API. Only two =
endpoint versions are allowed before a major version needs to be created. W=
hen a new major version is created , any deprecated endpoints MUST be remov=
ed.</p>
<p><span>You should consider the pros and cons of each versioning strategy,=
 and choose the one that suits your needs and preferences. You should also =
follow some best practices, such as minimizing breaking changes, documentin=
g your API versions, and deprecating old versions gracefully.&nbsp;</span><=
/p>
<p>The use of JSON&nbsp;instead of XML as a data format for APIs provides t=
he opportunity to make many changes in a backwards compatible fashion. &nbs=
p;The table below illustrates some typical types of changes and whether the=
y are backwardly compatible (non-breaking) or not. &nbsp;Note that the term=
 'operation' refers to the combination of HTTP verb and URI.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped tf-macro confluenceTable" data-tf-ready=3D"true">
<colgroup>
